Class StreamFixedList<T extends BaseEntity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fiftyone.mobile.detection.entities.stream.StreamBaseList<T>
      • fiftyone.mobile.detection.entities.stream.StreamFixedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of BaseEntity the list will contain
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDisposable, IFixedList<T>, IReadonlyList<T>, Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FixedCacheList

    public class StreamFixedList<T extends BaseEntity>
extends StreamBaseList<T>
implements IFixedList<T>
    Lists can be stored as a set of related objects entirely within memory, or the relevant objects loaded as required from a file or other permanent store as required. Delegate methods are used to create new instances of items to add to the list in order to avoid creating many inherited list classes for each type. Should not be referenced directly.
